<br>
We have a 65 SK who tanks, I'm the chanter and they make me bot my cleric (Ceyria) too.  Then we have 4 others to choose from to help flag folks, 63 rogue, 61 monk, 63 SK or a 65 paladin. Add to that the person or people that need the flagging. <br>
<br>
We run in and get in the back corner all together, clericbot on the horse, chanter on the stage, Vorne (the tank) in the center to attract aggro. All call the pets into the room (I have AA spent to control my pet, but still useful if your chanter brings in a pet). Chanter mezzes mobs close to the tank. Fascination works, target off the tank if you want. It can aggro the unmezzable ones to chase the chanter though, and any that resisted. If they chase, run down next to the tank and then mezz them. As soon as they're mezzed, stand right beside the tank and keep yourself in runes. Cleric uses HoT spells, and if it's bad, I'll use Divine Arbitration and then group HoT (unless the pally is there to wave heal). <br>
<br>
The key is to have everyone close, don't ping mobs, don't box out the melee (those benches suck), make sure the rogues have backs. The tank needs to target fast and folks need to assist. No time to taunt before breaking mezz, have the chanter stand close and suck it up, we're wiley and have ways to avoid damage.  After each round, return to the spots you first  were in so the tank gets aggro on next spawn. Chanter and cleric (if they're good on mana) should have a nuke up to toss in case of close calls. Make sure to have cure disease up for slows, or better yet, Radiant Cure or that earring from Chardok (forget name, but my cleric has one, free counteract disease and another that has free counteract poison). <br>
<br>
At the last mob of the 4th cycle, have the cleric and casters in the back of the room, where you enter, straight down the hall, and have the tank go up and establish aggro fast. Get him slowed. It's brutal, but once the shaman/chanter has done their job and slowed him, they're ok to die if you can't take the time or mana to heal them. You need the mana for the tank. Make sure the tank is healed and toss a HoT on them as the last mob is dying. I tend to keep them alive with HoT and remedy in case it has some good rounds. <br>
<br>
That's how we do it at least. Hope this helps some. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://jens-smileys3.netfirms.com/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src="http://www.capulus.org/fourgirls01.gif"><br> <b>CAPULUS</b><br>
