<br>
Shadow Knight (me)<br>
Rogue<br>
Necro<br>
Enchanter<br>
Cleric<br>
Mage<br>
<br>
We did the Trial of Exe. We stood in the corner to the left of the stage if you're facing it. As soon as a wave began, I would target and engage one of the stonegrabber mobs (any mob if their wasn't one). All I have to do was get aggro and keep it, as the 3 pets (nec, mag, and mine) did the damage along with the rogue. If mana permitted, people nuked.<br>
<br>
Before the mob would die (at around 10%) I would peel off and hit another and start on it. Forget taunting to get aggro before breaking mez, just hit the damn thing. The key is high DPS and speed in targetting and killing.<br>
<br>
We got close to losing a few times before the boss, but we managed to hold our own.<br>
<br>
Also, have someone with Counteract Disease up and ready to cure slow if you get it cast on you. Keep the DPS up!!<br>
<br>
When it came to the Executioner, we only had the enchanter die due to over nuke aggro. The exe hits hard and hits you with Armor Break at the start of the fight which REALLY downs your AC. Keep the tank alive, heal fast and take him down. There's no time limit on him, so just get him dead. <p><center><a href="http://www.equnleashed.com" target="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://members.cox.net/skoriksis/skor_sig.jpg" BORDER="0"></A><br><font size="1" FACE="verdana">Profiles: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24686" target="_blank">Skoriksis, 63 SK</a> - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24782" target="_blank">Cyranith, 51 Nec</a> - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52153" target="_blank">Vermiir, 40 Wiz</a></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#77839D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/beverquestpeople.showUserPublicProfile?gid=asphixxia>asphixxia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=9933FF>Lord Manson</font></span><br>  Posts: 695<br> <font color=#F7E5C3>(2/13/03 8:05:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://digital-decay.org/icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trial Flagging Strategy?</span><hr size=1> When I was pov/s flagged we had:<br>
<br>
Me - pal<br>
bard - AE slow works wonders in this... but will also give the bard lots of agro... the tank needs to be able to maintain and pick up agro very quickly.. &quot;ping pong&quot; agro so to speak, will usually result in failing.<br>
cleric<br>
rogue<br>
beast<br>
shaman<br>
<br>
Over all, I've noticed you need to pull at least 400dps all together to pass successfully. As for the final fight of the executioner..  I've heard of most groups kiting him around, because 60% of the time, the MT will die, just due to the cleric being low on mana after 4 waves of these mobs. Personally, I died when the executioner was at half life.. then rezzed back in after he was dead, and looted my mark. However.. Your body will need to be rezzed *TWICE*. Once to get you into the zone.. the second time to get you into the trial ring where you previously died.<br>
<br>
Basically, *IF* the tank can keep and maintain agro sufficiently, you will pass... otherwise, you're gonna have lots of problems.<br>
<br>
For a warrior , I suggest some very taunt heavy weapons.. don't worry about your dps, as much... just make sure you keep taunt.<br>
<br>
